13/02/2006
WASHINGTON, United States -- Foreign ministers of the Adriatic Charter countries -- Albania's Besnik Mustafaj, Croatia's Kolinda Grabar-Kitarovic and Macedonia's Ilinka Mitreva -- were due to begin a two-day meeting in Washington Monday (13 February), hosted by US Undersecretary of State Nicholas Burns. 
This is described as a regular meeting under the initiative, aimed at boosting the three countries' prospects for NATO membership. 
(Focus - 13/02/06; Makfax - 12/02/06)
